{{Unreferenced|date=July 2010}}
A "'''backlash'''" is an adverse reaction to something which has gained popularity, prominence, or influence. Although it can sometimes represent a categorical rejection of the idea, aesthetic, product, or fad in question, it is usually a reflection of a collective resentment of that thing's ubiquity in [[culture]] and [[Mass media|media]], rather than a denial of its existence. The term is commonly applied to gender and [[racial discrimination]] and [[religious discrimination]] against [[minority group|minority]] groups, as well, such as in response to certain events or circumstances.
==See also== * [[Pyrrhic victory]] * [[Streisand effect]] * [[Trump effect]]
